    <h1 style="text-align:center;">How Does It Work?</h1>
    <br>
    <br>
    <h3 style="text-align:center;color:blue;">For people who want to be hired</h3>
    <br>
    <p id="info">We at the team of JobFinder always want the best for you.
      We like to make sure that a person finds a job which he enjoys working in as it will
      increase his own productivity and also be beneficial for the company. But how do we achieve that?
      We have a very different approach in how we allocate people to a company for interviews. We look
      at the interests and expectations of an individual and pick out the best possible options for him/her.
      We also look at various other aspects such as previous work experience, area of preference for jobs etc.
      as parameters when it comes to suggesting the right jobs to you.This is what makes JobFinder
      such a trusted entity when it comes to selecting the right job.
    </p>

    <br>
    <br>
    <h3 style="text-align:center;color:red;">For people who want to hire</h3>
    <br>
    <p id="info">Our system has a filter basis which will make the task for companies like yours easier
      when it comes to performing interviews. We will select only those candidates who perfectly match
      and satisfy the company's requirements for the further internal processes. This will make your selection
      process much more easier and efficient and also reduce the cost.
    </p>
